Holotype COLOMBIA • 1 ♂ ; Cundinamarca Departament , La Calera ; [ 4°43′11″ N , 73°58′12″ W ];
30 Jun. 1978
; C. Hernandez leg.; ICN-Ar .

COLOR. Exemplar probably discolored. Carapace orange, darker in cephalic region (
Fig. 14A
). Labium, sternum and endites reddish brown. Chelicerae reddish brown. Legs I–IV yellow, darker at tarsi. Abdomen yellow with dark longitudinal spots (
Fig. 14A
).

PALP. Retrolateral tibial apophysis conical with apex lightly curved; cymbium with retrolateral projection; short embolus; ventral tegular process near the median apophysis; sperm duct in vertical position with secondary loop reaching the apex of the tegulum; median apophysis long and curved at the apex (
Fig. 14C–E
).

COLOR. Exemplar probably discolored. Coloration as in males of this species (
Fig. 14B
).
